author: Adia Robinson
title: La. governor warns state's health care system could be overwhelmed by early April
description: New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy and Louisiana Gov. John Bel Edwards appear on ABC's "This Week" to talk about how their states are responding to the coronavirus outbreak.
content:
Gov. John Bel Edwards said cases of novel coronavirus are expected to surge in Louisiana and overwhelm hospitals.
"We remain on a trajectory, really to overwhelm our capacity to deliver health care by the end of the first week of April," he said on ABC's "Th… [+3835 chars]
